#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:102
msgid "Optional. When the payment confirms, send the buyer here (a custom thank-you, a digital-download page, etc.) instead of staying on the order-received page. {order_id} and {order_key} are substituted — {order_key} only for a URL on this same site, so the order token is never leaked to a third-party domain. Leave empty for the default WooCommerce behaviour."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:105
msgid "How payments are verified"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:109
msgid "Auto-detect in WordPress — no server (recommended)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:110
msgid "Buyer taps “I’ve paid” — no server"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:111
msgid "Auto-detect via your xmr-pay agent (advanced)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:113
msgid "All three are non-custodial (funds go straight to your address). <strong>Auto-detect in WordPress</strong> needs no backend: WordPress scans the chain itself (with your view key, against a public node) and completes the order — no buyer action, nothing to run 24/7. <strong>Buyer taps “I’ve paid”</strong> is the lightest: the buyer submits the transaction ID and WordPress verifies it (no scanning). <strong>Agent</strong> uses the separate xmr-pay daemon you run. The “No-server settings” below (address, view key, nodes) apply to the two no-server options; the “Agent settings” apply only to Agent mode."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:116
msgid "No-server settings (Auto-detect & “I’ve paid”)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:118
msgid "Used by both no-server modes — “Auto-detect in WordPress” and “Buyer taps I’ve paid”. Your private view key stays on your own server (we never hold a spend key — funds go straight to your address). WordPress fetches transactions from a public node and verifies them itself."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:121
#: includes/class-xmrpay-setup.php:277
msgid "Your Monero address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:124
msgid "Your primary Monero address — buyers pay here. Each order gets a unique amount so payments can’t be confused."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:127
#: includes/class-xmrpay-setup.php:281
msgid "Private view key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:129
msgid "Your wallet’s PRIVATE VIEW key (not the spend key). View-only: it can see incoming payments but cannot spend. <strong>More private:</strong> instead of storing it here, put <code>define('XMRPAY_VIEW_KEY', '…');</code> in wp-config.php — then it stays out of the database, this screen, and backups. A value here is used only if the constant is not set."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:132
msgid "Monero node(s)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:135
msgid "Public node URL(s), comma-separated. Your own node first if you run one. Used only to fetch transactions and the chain height (it never sees your view key)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:138
#: includes/class-xmrpay-setup.php:300
msgid "Confirmations required"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:141
msgid "0 = accept as soon as it’s seen (fast, mempool); 1 = first block (~2 min); 10 = fully unlocked (safest for high value)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:145
msgid "Underpayment tolerance (XMR)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:148
msgid "Accept a payment that falls short by up to this much (dust/rounding). 0 = exact. It can never reach the price, so a near-zero payment never settles an order."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:151
#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:425
msgid "Check setup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:155
msgid "Agent settings (advanced)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-wc-gateway-xmrpay.php:157
msgid "Used only when the “Agent” mode is selected. The separate xmr-pay daemon you run (see docs/AGENT.md) holds your view key and does the scanning — this plugin only talks HTTP to it. Detection policy (confirmations, tolerance, expiry) is set ON the agent (XMR_MIN_CONFIRMATIONS, XMR_TOLERANCE_XMR, XMR_EXPIRY_HOURS). Leave blank if you use a no-server mode."
msgstr ""

